accessibility.text: Professions and work
pasted-image.tiff
Credentialing systems encourage “closure,” or the limiting of certain professions and titles only to those who work within the system.
Professions and work
pasted-image.tiff
Credentialing systems encourage “closure,” or the limiting of certain professions and titles only to those who work within the system.
Often these credentialing systems do not emphasize, teach, or even require the same skills as those actually needed for a job.

pasted-image.tiff
Credentialing systems encourage “closure,” or the limiting of certain professions and titles only to those who work within the system.
Often these credentialing systems do not emphasize, teach, or even require the same skills as those actually needed for a job.
E.g., take the difference between an MBA and what people learn on the job.
